HTML tables can adjust the padding inside the cells, and also the space between the cells

HTML table - cell padding
Cell padding is the space between the cell edges and the cell content
By default the padding is set to 0
To add padding on table cells, use the CSS padding property
Th, td {
Padding: 15px
}

To add padding only above the content, use th padding-top property
And the others sides with the padding-bottom, padding-left and paddding-right properties

HTML table - cell spacing
Cell spacing is the space between each cell
By defaul the space is set to 2 pixels
To change the space between table cells, use the CSS border-spacing property on the table
element
Table {
Border-spacing: 30px }
